freelancers.title: Backup a website's videos on Telegram
freelancers.caption:
🚨 This is a time sensitive project, so please hurry if interested 🚨

I'm looking for someone to backup the videos from a website to a private Telegram channel. The videos are currently hosted on another platform so I need someone who can transfer them from there to Telegram. The total size of the videos that need to be backed up is more than 10GB. I want this project to be completed with precision, and expect the videos to be backed up to a private Telegram channel, rather than an account. All the videos are easily leechable through yt-dlp supported links directly to Telegram and every single yt-dlp based bot can support this operation easily and very fastly.

I'm looking for someone who is skilled in computer science and data-related operations - someone who has strong knowledge of tools to successfully scrape the sources of the videos and several other details including captions and then to download and upload each and every vidoe and successfully caption them in a neat and organized way, sorted from the oldest video to the newest video, as a final product on a private Telegram channel to carry out this project. I'm aware that this may take some time (around 2-3 days), but I'm willing to provide the available resources to support the freelancer in order to get the job done, on time and with accuracy. 

I am looking for someone who can do this in the best shape and form, with absolute precision, not missing a signle video, for the lowest price offer. So far the best offer I've got is 40$... I am willing to find a better price than this, why? Because I intend to do many future and Similar projects with the person who carries out this task successfully... the future projects are infinite and can guarantee a constant income to the freelancer who chooses to complete this task successfully... most importantly, all of the future task will be 99% similar to this so they can be done with Trivial effort, with this single code that the freelancer, develops for this single project... so the next projects will be 99% easier and less time consuming and more profitable.

If you think you are a suitable candidate for this job, please get in touch with me. Can not wait to hear from sophisticated and astute freelancers, in the shortest time.

freelancers.title: رفع ایرادات پروژه
freelancers.caption:
توضیحات پروژه در فایل ضمیه شفافه و متن زیر ایرادیه که  گرفته شده 
to permit. The rejection is justified as follows:
The application documents you submitted were available to the responsible faculty for review and examination. The examination board comes to the conclusion that you meet the entry requirements for admission to the above-mentioned unfortunately not fulfill the master’s degree. You justify the rejection as follows:
The admission relevant bachelor's degree is computer science/mathematical/statistical oriented, however the statistical data analysis project report does not meet our minimum requirements:
Among many other minor bugs and sub-optimal parts, the main reason(s) for rejection is/are - your report does not contain a method description for the descriptive methods used
- In your description you practically only give 3 times 4 numbers: number, average speed, average weight per type of movement. This isn't really a descriptive analysis, you completely ignore all other aspects of the distribution of the data, e.g. B. You don't even notice the outliers in weight. Also, using one number to only show 4 numbers is not good.
- In your method description of the linear model, you neither go into the assumptions of a linear model nor explain how the model coefficients are estimated.
- During the evaluation it is unclear what you did. The scales of the chart are logarithmic, so did you perform a logarithmic transformation? Also, your regression lines are not linear. You can't just "do something" and make a number out of it without describing what you did. In a report you must be precise. Your reader needs to be able to understand 100% what you did.
